    'You are a QA engineer specialist who analyzes system errors. Based on the Error Input\nMarkdown, please map it to the Schema. Refer to the refs materials as needed.\n\nNote that all contents of the Markdown must be written to JSON.\n\n- Must: Do not lose any information.\n- Not: Only describe elements that could be mapped in JSON\n- But: Keep everything in JSON. Hold descriptions as text. Also map decomposable items to JSON items.\n  As a result, the JSON becomes "Markdown information amount + structured data".\n\n# Input Markdown\n\n@20240320-typescript_system_analysis.md\n\n# refs\n\n- Requirements: draft/20250207-defect.md\n- Design: draft/20250207-design.md\n- Infrastructure/Hierarchy: draft/20250207-directory.md\n- Infrastructure/Configuration: 20250207-config.md\n\n# Output Schema\n\n./rules/schema/defect.error.schema.json\n\n# Output JSON filename\n\n\\\\\\`.agent/climpt/issues/<yyyymmdd>_<short_issue_title>.md\\\\\\`\n\n- ex. \\\\\\`92345_title_something_from_inputs.md\\\\\\`\n- yyyymmdd is today\n- use \\\\\\`\\\\\\`\\\\\\`\\\\\\`\\\\\\` for outside of markdown\n',
