  "to/issue/f_project_strict.md":
    "# Issue Creation Prompt (Strict)\n\nThis prompt helps convert project information into strictly structured issues with enhanced validation.\n\n## Input\nThe input is a project breakdown containing:\n- Project details (required)\n- Main objectives (required)\n- Key deliverables (required)\n- Technical requirements (required)\n- Timeline estimates (required)\n- Dependencies (required)\n\n## Output\nThe output must be a strictly structured JSON file with:\n- Issue title (required, max 100 chars)\n- Description (required, min 50 chars)\n- Acceptance criteria (required, min 3 items)\n- Dependencies (required if specified in input)\n- Priority level (required, one of: P0, P1, P2)\n- Estimated effort (required, in story points)\n- Technical constraints (required)\n- Validation rules (required)\n\n## Instructions\n1. Strictly validate project breakdown format\n2. Create issues only for complete deliverables\n3. Enforce strict acceptance criteria format\n4. Require explicit dependency declarations\n5. Mandate priority assignment\n6. Require detailed effort estimation\n7. Enforce technical specification\n8. Validate all required fields ",
  "to/issue/defect_fix_markdown.md":
    'You are a specialist in defect remediation.\nTo achieve the functionality that was originally intended, you understand the error content and identify the issues that need to be resolved.\nThe identified issues are goal-oriented, defect-avoidant, and realistic.\n\nBased on the Input Json Schema, organize according to the "Organization Steps".\n\nWrite up the organized results as "Organization Description" and save to "Output Markdown".\nIf arguments are divided, splitting into multiple files is also recommended.\n\n# Organization Steps\n\n1. From Input, determine only one most critical issue 1-1. Select the issue with the highest severity\n2. Define the minimum fix goal for the most critical issue 2-1. Use mingoal to make only one place work correctly 2-2.\n   Confirm the existence of mingoal test 2-3. If there is no mingoal test, mark as "Not created"\n3. Define extended goals for the most critical issue 3-1. When mingoal is cleared, identify other functions within the same issue 3-2.\n   Narrow down to issues that can be cleared by the same method as mingoal and list them 3-3.\n   Identify and list functions corresponding to the listed issues 3-4.\n   Identify test code corresponding to the function list 3-5. If there is no test code, mark as "Not created"\n4. List error messages that will disappear when the most critical issue is resolved 4-1.\n   Reference logs and identify errors that should disappear after resolution 4-2.\n   Create a checklist to verify whether they have disappeared or not\n\n# Input Json Schema\n\n- 20250209_typescript_error_handling.json\n- defined schema by \\\\\\`./docs/defects.md\\\\\\`\n\n# refs\n\n- Requirements: draft/20250207-defect.md\n- Design: draft/20250207-design.md\n- Infrastructure/Hierarchy: draft/20250207-directory.md\n- Infrastructure/Configuration: 20250207-config.md\n- mingoal: \\\\\\`./docs/mingoal.md\\\\\\`\n- logs: \\\\\\`./logs/deno_check.log\\\\\\`, \\\\\\`./logs/deno.test.log\\\\\\`\n\n# use commands for following\n\n- Understanding changed files\n- Checking the contents of files that have errors\n- Running tests or applications for additional investigation as needed\n\n# Organization Description\n\n- Create the most critical issue name and issue summary\n  - The summary comprehensively explains the content of the problem issue, approximately 60 characters\n- mingoal\n  - Explain functions and tests\n  - Functions are explained including the expected responsibilities from pre and post processing\n  - Tests define success. If test code already exists, indicate the name of the test that should pass.\n- Extended goals\n  - List them\n    - For each list item, explain functions and tests\n    - Functions are explained including the expected responsibilities from pre and post processing\n    - Tests define success.\n      - If test code already exists, indicate the name of the test that should pass.\n      - If not, mark as "Not created" and describe the definition of success.\n- Error messages that will disappear\n  - List them\n    - System error message\n    - Check whether it has disappeared or not \\\\\\`[ ]\\\\\\`\n    - Note whether it will disappear with mingoal or extended goal\n- Confirmation file list\n  - List them\n  - Used as arguments for \\\\\\`deno test\\\\\\` or \\\\\\`deno check\\\\\\`\n\n# Output Markdown\n\n\\\\\\`.agent/climpt/issues/<yyyymmdd>-<short_issue_summary>.md\\\\\\`\n\n- \\\\\\`yyyymmdd\\\\\\` is today\n- use \\\\\\`\\\\\\`\\\\\\`\\\\\\`\\\\\\` for outside of markdown\n',
